benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/{customFieldId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve custom field audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: TC01 validates successful retrieval of audit logs with history for an existing custom field (200 OK, JSON array of AuditLog objects).
Empty Response: TC02 and TC12 validate 200 OK with an empty array when there are no audit logs or the regression case.
Authorization: TC06 and TC07 validate 401 Unauthorized for missing or invalid tokens.
Not Found/Error Handling: TC03 and TC04 verify 404 responses for non-existent custom field and orphaned account.
Parameter Validation / Edge Cases: TC05, TC10, TC15, TC16, TC17 cover invalid ID formats, extra path segments, missing IDs, boundary UUID values, and leading/trailing spaces.
Security: TC09 covers SQL injection attempt by ensuring 400/404 and no internal errors.
System Availability: TC08 simulates backend DB unavailability and expects 503 Service Unavailable.
Regression & Compatibility: TC12 and TC13 ensure regression correctness and backward compatibility with older clients.
Performance & Load: TC11 and TC14 cover performance on large audit logs and concurrent requests.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for API pagination (page/size, total counts, and paging links).
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling (e.g., 429 responses under burst load).
Caching Behavior: No tests checking caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or cache validation (304).
Authorization: No tests for insufficient permissions (403 Forbidden).
Edge-case robustness: No tests for exotic path values or encoded characters beyond known edge cases.
Content Negotiation: No tests validating Accept header behavior or non-JSON responses.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: validate page and pageSize with and without results, verify total counts and correct headers/links.
Add rate limiting tests: simulate burst requests and verify 429 responses per policy.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/If-None-Match behavior and 304 responses, plus Cache-Control headers.
Add 403 Forbidden tests: ensure proper error when authenticated user lacks permissions.
Extend edge-case tests: include encoded path parameters and additional boundary values.
Test Accept header variations: ensure proper handling of unsupported Accept values (406).
Align server error codes with guidelines: consider 500 Internal Server Error for backend failures, ensuring no leakage of internal details.
Documentation/data: ensure the AuditLog fields beyond the required subset are validated in TC01 (structure correctness) and update tests if the schema evolves.
